all hail the pasta gods! Homemade pasta with mushroom confit. ğŸ™ŒğŸ™Œ 3/4 cup flour
1 large egg (if small or med use less flour)
1 Tablespoon of oil

Make a well with flour and slowly incorporate egg and oil with surrounding flour. Knead for a minimum of 10 min. Add water if douch is dry and flour if dough is too wet. Roll out very thin then tear pieces off of desired size. Then mix with emeril lagasse's wild mushroom confit recipe. TA-DAAA!
You can also use a bit of truffle oil.

Being in NYC there are no shortage of bagel places to fill this wish! What food brings you joy? What person brings you joy in your life? Your joy does not have a limit like filling up a gas tank. You have the possibility for unlimited joy! Comment below and declare you are going to do this on a happy day! This is a fun way to eat bagels and lox! Its my 7 Layer Bagel and Lox Dip!! Cheers to recipes that celebrate you!!!
(Click profile link for recipe) or https://www.chophappy.com/recipes/course/starters/everything-bagel-seasoning-7-layer-dip/
Ingredients
1 cup hummus
2 tomatoes (chopped)
16 ounces whipped cream cheese
1/2 lemon (juice)
4 scallions (chopped)
4 ounces smoked salmon slices
1/4 cups capers (drained)
8 ounces sour cream
4 tablespoons everything bagel seasoning (2 tbsp for hummus and 2 tbsp for top layer)
1 teaspoon salt and pepper

I had the opportunity to try a spirit called Baijiu and it is unlike anything I have had before. Floral, fruity & funky. Very unique! I created this cocktail to play with those notes of the Baijiu and this is what I got! Hope you dig it.
.
â€¢ 2oz Ming River Sichuan Baijiu
â€¢ 1oz Rhubarb & Elderfower Cordial
â€¢ .5oz Mulled Pineapple
â€¢ 2oz Tonic Water
â€¢ .5oz Lime
â€¢ 1 Dash Orange Blossom
â€¢ 2 Dash Lemon & Lavender Bitters Kinsip
â€¢ .25 Tube Betters Miraculous Foamer
â€¢ Raspberry & Orange Oil
.
.
